AB In this article, we review applications of covariance-based structural
   equation modeling (SEM) in the Journal of Advertising (JA) starting with
   the first issue in 1972. We identify 111 articles from the earliest
   application of SEM in 1983 through 2015, and discuss important
   methodological issues related to the following aspects: confirmatory
   factor analysis (CFA), causal modeling, multiple group analysis,
   reporting, and guidelines for interpretation of results. Moreover, we
   summarize some issues related to varying terminology associated with
   different SEM methods. Findings indicate that the use of SEM in the JA
