   advertising, much has yet to be discovered about how the effects of
   multiple media combine to shape sales response. Two challenges related
   to the investigation of media interaction effects are their complex
   nature and their specification in a sales response model. The authors
   adopt a flexible modeling approach, multivariate adaptive regression
   splines (MARS), which captures parsimoniously complex interaction
   effects and facilitates their measurement and interpretation. Analysis
   of multiple data sets on brand sales and media spending points to the
   following typology of media interaction effects: (1) synergistic
